* Tue Jul 14 2026 Mike Riddle <mike@sicura.us> - 2.0.0
- BREAKING: Replaced the `deferred_resources::packages`, `::users`,
  `::groups`, and `::files` classes with a single `deferred_resources` class
  that accepts a Hash of resources keyed by resource type
  - Any native resource type may be used and any mix of resource types may be
    passed in the same Hash
  - A per-type `default_options` parameter replaces the per-class options
  - The `auto_include` parameter has been removed
  - Existing catalog resources can be overridden per resource by setting the
    reserved `override: true` option on an entry; all attributes specified on
    the entry are forced onto the existing resource and an attribute
    explicitly set to undef (`~`) is removed from it (this replaces the old
    `update_existing_resources`/`invalidates` mechanism)
- Resource type names are case-normalized and duplicate type entries fail at
  compile time instead of producing duplicate resource declarations
- Entries that reference the same underlying resource via their title or an
  explicit 'name' attribute fail at compile time instead of being processed
  in a nondeterministic order
- Fix a catalog failure (duplicate resource/alias error) when a deferred
  resource's namevar collides with an existing catalog resource declared
  under a different title
- Unknown resource types are skipped with a log message instead of failing
  the catalog run

